    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nStartup screen is lost on startup when cursorcolumn and signcolumn are set. Also, on the rare occasion, you can see the intro screen flicker and it disappears. This is more obvious when I bootstrap lazy.nvim after setting the two settings (presumably when the init is more involved).\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean -u ~/.config/nvim/init.lua where `init.lua`:\r\n\r\n    vim.opt.cursorcolumn = true\r\n    vim.opt.signcolumn = \"yes\"\r\n    -- end of file\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIntro screen should be retained and there should be no occasional flickering. \n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.8.3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnot sure\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nAlacritty 0.11.0 (8dbaa0bb)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty-direct\n\n### Installation\n\nArch official repository",
